Title: Mariathasan2018_PDL1_treatment
Description: Processed RNA-seq data, quantified as counts and TPM, for bladder cancer samples pre anti-PDL1 immunotherapy. Information on patient's tumor mutational burden and response to anti-PD1 treatment is also provided. Represented as a SummarizedExperiment; derived from IMvigor210CoreBiologies R package (Mariathasan et al., Nature, 2018) under the CC-BY license.
DataProvider: IMvigor210CoreBiologies package;  Mariathasan S, Turley S, Nickles D et al., â€œTGF-b attenuates tumor response to PD-L1 blockade by contributing to exclusion of T cells.

Title: opt_models
Description: Cancer-specifc model feature parameters learned, for each quantitative descriptor, during training using multi-task learning with randomized cross-validation repeated 100 times. For each quantitative descriptor, 1000 models are available (100 per task).

Title: opt_xtrain_stats
Description: Cancer-specific features mean and standard deviation of the training set used during randomized cross-validation repeated 100 times. It is required for normalization of input feautres.

Title: TCGA_mean_pancancer
Description: Mean of the TPM expression of each gene across all TCGA cancer types. It is required for normalization of input TPM gene expression data.

Title: TCGA_sd_pancancer
Description: Standard deviation of the TPM expression of each gene across all TCGA cancer types. It is required for normalization of input TPM gene expression data.

Title: cor_scores_genes
Description: Character string with genes used to define correlated scores of immune response.

Title: intercell_networks
Description: Cancer-specific intercellular networks, including a pan-cancer network.

Title: lr_frequency_TCGA
Description: Frequency of each ligand-receptor pair feature across the whole TCGA database.

Title: group_lrpairs
Description: Information to group ligand-receptor pairs because of sharing the same gene either as ligand or receptor.

Title: scores_signature_genes
Description: Gene signatures for each score of immune response: CYT, TLS, IFNy, Ayers_expIS, Tcell_inflamed, Roh_IS, Davoli_IS, chemokines, IMPRES, MSI, RIR.
